'It does get a little bit stinky,' he quipped on the Today show on Monday. 

'It has been dry-cleaned a couple of times and it gets harder and harder to wear.'

The experiment was a show of support for Wilkinson who gave a speech 12 months ago on the pressures and scrutiny women in television faced on a daily basis. 

'Some people have called it reverse sexism, or whatever it is, I don’t know whether it is that because can sexism be women judging mainly other women?' Stefanovic said. 

'I think in this situation for women on TV, it’s mainly women judging women and what they wear.'

Wilkinson said: 'From the emails I've received in this job, most have been from women and I don't know how we got into that space where it leans to a lack of support.'

